    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f5021410_feaa50bd",
        "filename": "common/proto/milo/manifest_diff.proto",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 27,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-26T16:33:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why do we need to distinguish MODIFIED and DIFF in Stat? FWIU the difference between them is that if DIFF, then the delta is available. I think that ((state\u003d\u003dMODIFIED) \u003d\u003e (delta may be available)) is simpler than ((stat\u003d\u003dDIFF) \u003d\u003d (delta is available)). Users that don\u0027t care about delta and want to know if a thing changed, wouldn\u0027t have to check for both DIFF and MODIFIED. If we remove DIFF, that would be one state less.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 27,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 27,
        "endChar": 8
      },
      "revId": "bdd3005e4bd1ef2b18817e2052f9ca2c99b3c392",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fb2e36af_5f0fb452",
        "filename": "common/proto/milo/manifest_diff.proto",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 27,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-09-26T23:02:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "However, most users do actually care about this distinction, so it\u0027s easier to have the differentiated states. I changed these to a bit mask however so that DIFF is 8|MODIFIED, so users who don\u0027t care about the distinction can always mask off the MODIFIED bit.",
      "parentUuid": "f5021410_feaa50bd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 27,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 27,
        "endChar": 8
      },
      "revId": "bdd3005e4bd1ef2b18817e2052f9ca2c99b3c392",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
